# Running the Project with Docker

To run this project using Docker, follow the steps below:

## Prerequisites

Ensure you have the following installed on your system:

- Docker version 22.13.1 or later
- Docker Compose version 1.29.2 or later

## Steps to Build and Run

1. Clone the repository:

   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/ssahibsingh/React_E-Commerce
   cd React_E-Commerce
   ```

2. Build and start the Docker containers:

   ```bash
   docker-compose up --build
   ```

3. Access the application in your browser at `http://localhost:3000`.

## Configuration

- The application runs on port `3000` as defined in the `docker-compose.yml` file.
- Ensure any required environment variables are set in a `.env` file if needed.

## Notes

- The `Dockerfile` is optimized for production builds.
- The `docker-compose.yml` file sets up a single service for the application.

For further assistance, refer to the [Docker documentation](https://docs.docker.com/).